Heatmap of composite and single genotypers

composite_loci_accuracy_plt <- composite_accuracy_df %>% 
  calculate_summary_df() %>% 
  gg_summary_hla_accuracy(color_label = "Accuracy")
composite_loci_accuracy_plt

Difference between composite and single genotypers

composite_loci_difference_plt <- composite_accuracy_df %>% 
  calculate_summary_df() %>% 
  select(-sd, - se) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = "genotyper", values_from = "mean_accuracy") %>% 
  pivot_longer(contains(c("arcasHLA", "hlaminer", "optitype", "phlat")), names_to = "genotyper", values_to = "genotyper_accuracy") %>% 
  mutate(mean_accuracy = composite - genotyper_accuracy) %>% 
  gg_summary_hla_accuracy(color_label = "Composite -\nindividual\ngenotyper\naccuracy") +
  scale_fill_gradientn(colors = RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(11, "BrBG"), limits = c(-0.25,0.25), na.value = "transparent", oob=squish)
Scale for 'fill' is already present. Adding another scale for 'fill', which will replace the existing scale.
composite_loci_difference_plt

Locus averaging

averaged_composite_accuracy <- composite_accuracy_df %>% 
  locus_average_accuracy() 
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'sample', 'field'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'sample', 'class', 'field'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

composite_average_difference_plt <- averaged_composite_accuracy %>%

  mutate(mean_accuracy = composite - genotyper_accuracy) %>%

Combined plots

loci_plt <- plot_grid(
  composite_loci_accuracy_plt,
  composite_loci_difference_plt,
  ncol = 1,
  align = "v",
  axis = "lr"
)

average_plt <- plot_grid(
  composite_average_accuracy_plt,
  composite_average_difference_plt,
  ncol = 1,
  align = "v",
  axis = "lr"
)

plot_grid(
  plot_grid(
    runtime_plt,
    average_plt,
    ncol = 1,
    align = "v",
    axis = "lr"
  ),
  loci_plt,
  nrow = 1,
  align = "h",
  axis = "tb"
)

plot_grid(
  runtime_plt,
  composite_loci_accuracy_plt,
  composite_loci_difference_plt,
  composite_average_accuracy_plt,
  composite_average_difference_plt,
  ncol = 1,
  align = "v",
  axis = "lr",
  rel_heights = c(1,1,1,0.6,0.6)
)
